{"id":1763,"date":"2022-04-06T05:05:39","date_gmt":"2022-04-06T10:35:39","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/?p=1763"},"modified":"2022-05-27T07:24:39","modified_gmt":"2022-05-27T12:54:39","slug":"car-maintenance-tips","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/car-maintenance-tips\/","title":{"rendered":"10 Basic Car Maintenance Tips Every Car Owner Should Know"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Having a car feels like having another member of the family. Nowadays many individuals are very much fond of cars. People either drive their family car, which has been passed down from their parents, or they purchase a brand new car. Knowing good and effective car maintenance tips is a must if you are looking for a smooth performance by your car. Regular maintenance is required to keep a car running smoothly. Basic car maintenance tips for novices will come in handy here. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This allows the automobile owner to be aware of any issues that may affect their car&#8217;s performance while on the road and to address them. <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Professionals or those who are familiar with car anatomy have very good car care tips for their four-wheelers. However, not everyone will have the opportunity to learn everything there is to know about car maintenance tips. Therefore, we have prepared this blog for all of you to have a better understanding and knowledge of it. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">But before we jump into that, let&#8217;s have a better understanding of the importance of maintaining a car and why we need it. <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Because you have invested thousands of rupees in your car, you must ensure that it is properly maintained. However, there are many other reasons to maintain your car and keep it in the best shape and conditions one possibly can. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You need to understand the types of car maintenance and all the necessary do&#8217;s and don&#8217;ts regarding it. <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You can avoid a variety of car problems simply by following the recommended maintenance schedule. When you&#8217;re traveling by car, the last thing you want to happen is for your car to break down. Maintaining all the systems and other components regularly can help you avoid costly repairs.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A car breakdown late at night on a quiet road might be quite dangerous. When you&#8217;re stopped on a quiet road, you never know what will happen. Regular maintenance lowers the chances of a car breakdown, and your car will be in excellent shape to carry you on your journey. For a solid grip on the road, it&#8217;s critical to check the treads and air pressure of your tires. It plays a very important role in the comforts of your journey. <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Regular maintenance is quite inexpensive, but unexpected repairs and replacements can be costly. Parts of a car will not suddenly stop working or functioning without any issue or reason. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When you overlook car maintenance, minor issues might arise, which can escalate into serious issues if you continue to disregard car maintenance. Regular car maintenance allows you to check for indicators of small issues such as cracks, leaks, excessive friction wear, and tear. If you pay attention to these details and make repairs, you can save the part and avoid having to replace it for a long time. Car maintenance, in some ways, extends the life of the engine and other components and lowers the need for replacement. As a result, it aids in the reduction of repair expenses.<\/span><\/p>\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_50 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-transparent ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<div class=\"ez-toc-title-container\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Table of Contents<\/p>\n<span class=\"ez-toc-title-toggle\"><\/span><\/div>\n<nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-2'><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/car-maintenance-tips\/#Now_let%E2%80%99s_have_a_look_at_10_basic_car_maintenance_tips_every_car_owner_should_know\" title=\"Now, let&#8217;s have a look at 10 basic car maintenance tips every car owner should know:\">Now, let&#8217;s have a look at 10 basic car maintenance tips every car owner should know:<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3'><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/car-maintenance-tips\/#Take_help_from_the_user%E2%80%99s_handbook\" title=\"Take help from the user&#8217;s handbook\">Take help from the user&#8217;s handbook<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/car-maintenance-tips\/#Keep_checking_your_tyre_pressure_and_balance\" title=\"Keep checking your tyre pressure and balance\">Keep checking your tyre pressure and balance<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/car-maintenance-tips\/#Keep_changing_your_oil_filter\" title=\"Keep changing your oil filter\">Keep changing your oil filter<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/car-maintenance-tips\/#Clean_the_outside_of_your_engine\" title=\"Clean the outside of your engine\">Clean the outside of your engine<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/car-maintenance-tips\/#Headlights_must_be_protected\" title=\"Headlights must be protected\">Headlights must be protected<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/car-maintenance-tips\/#Have_maintenance_of_the_battery\" title=\"Have maintenance of the battery\">Have maintenance of the battery<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-8\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/car-maintenance-tips\/#Maintain_your_fuel_efficiency\" title=\"Maintain your fuel efficiency\">Maintain your fuel efficiency<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-9\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/car-maintenance-tips\/#Spark_plugs_must_be_replaced_when_necessary\" title=\"Spark plugs must be replaced when necessary\">Spark plugs must be replaced when necessary<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-10\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/car-maintenance-tips\/#Maintain_a_clean_interior\" title=\"Maintain a clean interior\">Maintain a clean interior<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-11\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/car-maintenance-tips\/#Clean_and_maintain_your_cooling_system\" title=\"Clean and maintain your cooling system&#xA0;\">Clean and maintain your cooling system&#xA0;<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-1'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-12\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/car-maintenance-tips\/#Conclusion\" title=\"Conclusion\">Conclusion<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Now_let%E2%80%99s_have_a_look_at_10_basic_car_maintenance_tips_every_car_owner_should_know\"><\/span>Now, let&#8217;s have a look at 10 basic car maintenance tips every car owner should know:<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Take_help_from_the_user%E2%80%99s_handbook\"><\/span><b>Take help from the user&#8217;s handbook<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The user&#8217;s handbook is the first and most important guide you should consult before beginning to follow car maintenance advice. The user handbook is of great help for new car owners who need help and guidance with new car maintenance tips. You&#8217;ll discover item-by-item information about your car here. User manuals are also easily available online on the car manufacturer&#8217;s website. <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This helps in urgent situations if you are not able to find the hard copy of your user handbook. <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you want to understand more about your car, treat the user handbook as a holy book. A lot of the difficulties and issues can be easily resolved by consulting the owner&#8217;s manual.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Keep_checking_your_tyre_pressure_and_balance\"><\/span>Keep checking your tyre pressure and balance<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tyre rotation is essential for maintaining your car&#8217;s safety and efficiency. This helps in improving the steering response of your car. It also smoothens the quality of the car. Rotating your tyres allows them to wear evenly and helps to improve the life of the tyres. It is very essential to check the tyres pressure of your car at least once or twice a month and it is even mandatory if there&#8217;s a trip planned. <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There are different types of tyre pressure and balance according to what car you own and many other factors. Your tyre pressure should be more or less than the mentioned pressure. This is a very important point, especially for Indian roads. You need to keep updating the pressure and balance of your tyres keeping in mind the conditions of Indian roads. And for that, you need basic knowledge about car maintenance tips India which will help you in situations like this. The amount of air pressure required for your car&#8217;s tyres will be specified in the owner&#8217;s handbook.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Keep_changing_your_oil_filter\"><\/span>Keep changing your oil filter<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Your car is a complicated machine with several little and large components. Because an automobile is a moving machine, it is unavoidable that several moving parts are involved. A car cannot run well without lubrication; it is present to guarantee that these parts operate smoothly. This is where the use of oil and oil filters comes into play. An oil filter maintains the oil clean and free of contaminants.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Clean_the_outside_of_your_engine\"><\/span>Clean the outside of your engine<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cleaning the external engine of your car is just as vital as cleaning the inside engine. Even tiny debris in the wrong spot can damage your engine if it is not cleaned properly. Some oil may slip into your brake fluid, for example, while you are monitoring it. Brake damage is possible as a result of this. As a result, at least once a month, check your brake fluid levels.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Headlights_must_be_protected\"><\/span>Headlights must be protected<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When you park in front of a level surface once a month, turn on your headlights to make sure they&#8217;re both operating and in the right place. This is one of those car exterior care tips<\/span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">which is very mandatory for a smooth driving experience. By strolling around your automobile and looking at your parking lights, visually verify both turn signals and turn signals. To ensure that your brake lights are operational, have a friend stand behind the car while you engage the brakes.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Have_maintenance_of_the_battery\"><\/span>Have maintenance of the battery<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Use the owner&#8217;s manual and, if necessary, the internet to learn the fundamentals of a car battery. You must be aware of the location of your car battery. The next step is to learn how to detach the battery safely and clean the terminal contacts as needed. Always remember to unplug the battery&#8217;s negative terminal first. This will effectively turn off the power and lessen the risk of an accident. Clean the contacts with a battery-safe brush before reconnecting. Connecting the positive first this time is the way to go. Cleaning the battery now and then can help it last longer.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Maintain_your_fuel_efficiency\"><\/span><b>Maintain your fuel efficiency<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It&#8217;s no secret that keeping your automobile in good shape will help you get better mileage. Maintaining fuel economy is also more cost-effective. Your car&#8217;s mileage suffers greatly as a result of constant speed changes and reckless driving. In the long term, it reduces the life of your car&#8217;s engine. As a result, your automobile will not operate smoothly, you will spend more time in the garage than usual, and so on. <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Do not rely on your car to transport large items regularly. Remember that the heavier you are, the less mileage you will get. If you own a business that requires you to move big goods daily, you should consider purchasing a car that is suitable for the job. Otherwise, your car&#8217;s mileage is likely to be harmed.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Spark_plugs_must_be_replaced_when_necessary\"><\/span><b>Spark plugs must be replaced when necessary<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The efficiency of your car&#8217;s engine could be affected by spark plugs. They&#8217;re in charge of igniting the gas-air mixture that drives your car. As a result, when the spark plugs fail, the engine loses power and is unable to perform at its best. So have your spark plugs checked by a professional, and if they&#8217;re faulty, have them replaced.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Maintain_a_clean_interior\"><\/span><b>Maintain a clean interior<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Spending money on a car wash every two days is not essential. Keeping the interior dust-free with a simple vacuum cleaner is also a good idea. In today&#8217;s market, there is a plethora of unique cleaning products. For instance, a blob of scented slime can be used to clean hard-to-reach areas like air vents, the base of a gear stick, or the space beneath the steering wheel.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Clean_and_maintain_your_cooling_system\"><\/span><b>Clean and maintain your cooling system&#xA0;<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">To operate smoothly and effectively, your car&#8217;s cooling system and radiator must be clean. With normal wear and tear, a deposit forms on the radiator, causing the cooling system to malfunction. A radiator flush is a simple and inexpensive way to keep your cooling system in good repair. Check your car&#8217;s manual to see if the radiator has to be flushed once a year or every two years.<\/span><\/p>\n<h1><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Conclusion\"><\/span>Conclusion<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h1>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Frequent car maintenance extends the life of your vehicle. You can monitor fluid levels, filters, and the wear and tear of various parts, among other things. All of these things are necessary for your car to run well. If you continue to drive without performing routine maintenance, your car will eventually break down, causing major difficulty. <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Things aren&#8217;t that difficult when it comes to car upkeep. Your car only needs to be properly maintained to lengthen its life. Furthermore, because of its condition, it has a higher resale value. If you follow the above-mentioned car maintenance tips then you will surely understand how to maintain your car to last many years.<\/span><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Having a car feels like having another member of the family. Nowadays many individuals are very much fond of cars. People either drive their family car, which has been passed down from their parents,&#46;&#46;&#46;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":200027,"featured_media":2284,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[1],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1763"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/200027"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=1763"}],"version-history":[{"count":7,"href":"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1763\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":2673,"href":"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1763\/revisions\/2673"}],"wp:featuredmedia":